This software is provided strictly for "learning and reference." It is strictly prohibited to copy, deploy, run, or integrate the code into any other projects; it is also strictly prohibited to use it for academic publications, patent applications, or stripping out core logic.
> Special Clause (REF + SL):
> The "distribution ban" under REF is lifted only when your derivative work meets the "Substantive Innovation Standard" (i.e., adding independent logic and rewriting more than 30% of the core code). Once lifted, your distribution behavior must fully comply with the requirements of [SL] Same-License. Modified versions that do not meet this standard are strictly prohibited from being distributed in any form.
